<details class="gov-details halo-panel">
    <summary class="gov-details__summary">DepotDownloader (GitHub): install, login and download</summary>
    <div class="gov-details__text">
        <p class="gov-body">
            DepotDownloader is an open-source CLI for pulling depots from Steam.
            Official repo (source + releases):
            <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader/releases">https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader/releases</a>
        </p>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Install</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">
                <strong>Get DepotDownloader</strong>:
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body">Download a prebuilt release from GitHub: <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader/releases">https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader/releases</a></li>
                    <li class="gov-body">Windows: install via winget (<code>winget install SteamRE.DepotDownloader</code>)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="gov-body">
                Ensure you have a compatible .NET runtime installed (see the GitHub README).
            </li>
            <li class="gov-body">
                Extract/apply the tool to a permanent folder, e.g. <code>C:\Tools\DepotDownloader</code>.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Run the generated command</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">Open a terminal in the DepotDownloader folder.</li>
            <li class="gov-body">
                Paste the generated command and replace:
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body"><code>&lt;install-dir&gt;</code> with the desired install folder</li>
                    <li class="gov-body"><code>&lt;user&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;pass&gt;</code> with your Steam credentials</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="gov-body">
                If Steam Guard prompts occur, complete them as instructed; then rerun the command.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Useful links</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body"><a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader">DepotDownloader GitHub home</a></li>
                    <li class="gov-body"><a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/SteamRE/DepotDownloader/releases">DepotDownloader releases</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Common issues</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body">“No manifest available” likely indicates Steam does not provide that manifest for download.</li>
                    <li class="gov-body">If a depot fails to download, confirm you own the content in Steam.</li>
                    <li class="gov-body">If output appears stuck, allow time for verification—downloads can pause.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>
</details>
